        "created_at": "2018-10-25T03:02:35.647Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019d like to know how I can go about debugging why FDB is or is not moving data. A lot of times a particular process would show up with a ton of CPU and storage queues would go up (throughput suffers), we can pull back on the traffic but DD doesn\u2019t seem to be moving data away from it (I know for a fact that if i just kill -9 the process, the cluster immediately behaves and since this is a double redundancy cluster, it\u2019s not a write hotspot since exactly one SS is hot).</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2018-10-25T03:02:35.647Z",
